                <h1>Do Protective Orders Appear on Background Checks?</h1>
                <p>Protective orders can indeed show up on background checks, particularly when those checks include court records. These orders may indicate potential safety concerns and can influence decisions in employment, housing, and legal matters. Understanding how protective orders affect background checks is crucial for anyone involved.</p>
